==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cudden
<hw>Cud"den</hw> <pr>(k?d"d'n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[For sense 1,
cf. Scot. <ets>cuddy</ets> an ass; for sense 2, see 3d
<er>Cuddy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A clown; a low rustic; a
dolt.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The slavering <qex>cudden</qex>, propped upon his staff.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The coalfish. See 3d
<er>Cuddy</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cuddle</ent>⟦br⟧
